Model Minority

The Harmful Stereotype of the Model Minority

The Model Minority stereotype is a harmful and pervasive belief in the United States that Asian Americans are successful and hardworking, and therefore serve as a positive precedent for other minority groups to follow. However, this stereotype erases the diversity of experienced within the Asian American community and created unrealistic expectations for individuals who are not part of the so-called "model minority"



Why it matters

While it may seem like a positive stereotype, the model minority myth is concerning and harmful in several ways. For once, it masks the discrimination and racism that Asian Americans face in their daily lives. The stereotype also places undue pressure on Asian Americans to succeed academically and professionally, often at the expense of their mental and emotional well-being. Additionally, it erases the diversity within the Asian American community and perpetuates the idea that all Asian Americans are the same
